cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO

The paper deals with gaze estimation, which is a problem in computer vision and human-computer interaction. The method proposed involves using a consumer RGB depth sensor, which falls under the category of computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves human-computer interaction, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and fitting of facial features, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also involves regression from appearance of eyes, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves pose estimation, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics).
